<subSubSection id="C340650393708876FF63FDFBFE9AFD0B" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE5368893708876FF63FDFBFE9AFD0B" blockId="4.[173,659,606,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FF63FDFBFEC7FD5B" bold="true" box="[197,301,632,653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The black humeral margin and the black elytral discal maculae will conveniently distinguish the members of this species from its congeners (
<figureCitation id="13612A0D93708876FEBAFD4BFE8FFD0B" box="[284,357,712,733]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,237,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,193,1649]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[172,1193,193,1649]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 61–64. Habitus. 61) Diutius gallerucoides; 62) Diutius pallidus; 63) Akonesis vittatis; 64) Akonesis pictipennis." pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C340650393708876FF63FD60FE51FB77" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE5368893708876FF63FD60FDA8FBE0" blockId="4.[173,659,606,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FF63FD60FE7AFD2E" bold="true" box="[197,400,739,760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Redescription. Size</emphasis>
: Length 11.0 mm; width 4.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FEAEFD7EFEABFCC4" bold="true" box="[264,321,765,786]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation id="13612A0D93708876FE28FD7EFE32FCC4" box="[398,472,765,786]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,237,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,193,1649]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[172,1193,193,1649]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 61–64. Habitus. 61) Diutius gallerucoides; 62) Diutius pallidus; 63) Akonesis vittatis; 64) Akonesis pictipennis." pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FE42FD7EFDB3FCC4" bold="true" box="[484,601,765,786]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Integument</emphasis>
: Cranium light brown; pronotum yellow; elytra mostly yellow, humerus, humeral margin, and basal region of epipleural margin black, with 2 preapical black maculae; femora yellow, tibiae and tarsi brown; pterothorax and abdomen brown. 
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FDA6FC01FDDCFC41" bold="true" box="[512,566,898,919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes as wide as frons (25:25); capitular antennomeres slen- der (
<figureCitation id="13612A0D93708876FF7DFC34FEC9FC1A" box="[219,291,951,972]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[197,238,1224,1243]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,194,1200]" captionTargetId="figure-220@8.[172,1193,193,1200]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 47–52. Akonesis vittatis. 47) Head, frontal view; 48) Head, ventral view; 49) Antenna; 50) Mouthparts;" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FE9EFC34FE6BFC1A" bold="true" box="[312,385,951,972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum quadrate (70:70) (
<figureCitation id="13612A0D93708876FF15FC51FF10FC31" box="[179,250,978,999]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[197,238,1368,1387]" captionTargetBox="[174,1163,203,1350]" captionTargetId="figure-110@6.[172,1193,183,1363]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 30–42. Morphological structures. 30) Akonesis vittatis, pronotum; 31) Akonesis pictipennis, pronotum; 32) Diutus pallidus, pronotum; 33) Crusbatus spinosus, pronotum; 34) D. pallidus, antenna; 35) Diutus gallerucoides, antenna; 36) C. spinosus, antenna; 37) D. pallidus, tegmen; 38) D. pallidus, phallus; 39) C. spinosus, spicular fork; 40) C. spinosus, male, pygidium; 41) C. spinosus, tegmen; 42) C. spinosus, phallus." pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), lateral tubercle prominent; epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous puncures absent; 1° setae absent. 
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FD84FB84FD61FBCA" bold="true" box="[546,651,1031,1052]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available for observation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5368893708876FF63FBBFFEC1FBBA" blockId="4.[173,659,606,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FF63FBBFFEC3FB87" bold="true" box="[197,297,1084,1105]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Variation.</emphasis>
The 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD0193708876FEC1FBBFFE15FB87" box="[359,511,1084,1105]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
examined are quite similar.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5368893708876FF63FBF2FE51FB77" blockId="4.[173,659,606,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FF63FBF2FE8CFB50" bold="true" box="[197,358,1137,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Natural History.</emphasis>
The specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="499EF86A93708876FD95FBF2FD79FB50" box="[563,659,1137,1158]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
was collected during March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C340650393708876FF63FB25FDCCFAB5" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE5368893708876FF63FB25FE1AFADD" blockId="4.[173,659,606,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="B92EEA9A93708876FF63FB25FEADFB6D" bold="true" box="[197,327,1190,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Distribution.</emphasis>
In addition to the 
<typeStatus id="54E1882A93708876FDABFB25FDD3FB6D" box="[525,569,1190,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">type</typeStatus>
, I examined a specimen from (
<figureCitation id="13612A0D93708876FE3DFB42FE02FB00" box="[411,488,1217,1238]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[197,229,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[175,1193,189,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[173,1194,189,1562]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 59. Distribution of Diutus gallerucoides, Diutus pallidus, Akonesis pictipennis, and Akonesis vittatis." pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
